 :tx/rationale "ADR-024 OBSERVATION 4: SESSION-PHASE HABITUATION. The LLM's context window has two regimes. EARLY CONTEXT (high learning rate): everything is new, command names and output format teach, optimal output is RICH (Demonstrate strategy). LATE CONTEXT (low learning rate): LLM has internalized the interface, repeating 'store: 55K datoms' for the 20th time wastes attention on facts already compressed into the latent representation. Optimal output is SPARSE (Signal strategy). The transition is NOT a function of turn count — it's a function of the LLM's DEMONSTRATED COMPREHENSION, measurable by whether the LLM's commands are correct. This is repetition suppression from neuroscience applied to the CLI output layer."
